<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: [It seems] that I've been on the same DL with [a very late-game unique who doesn't show up until a certain plot event happens]! Savefile available if desired. <p>
<strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: Known uniques list is carried over from game to game, listing all of the ones who are alive or dead.  If you've ever seen [that guy] at all in a previous game he'll show up on the list. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./ZasVid">ZasVid</a></strong>: He will show up also if you have ever researched him in beastmaster's shop. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: Good point, since it's just an extension of the monster memory. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: Good points all. However: 
</p>

    <ol type="1">

    <li>
<p>
I've never seen the known uniques list to carry over. I just tested it, in fact, by creating a new character. Her known uniques list is completely empty, as is her monster memory (except for the two townspeople in her line of sight when she was "born".) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
I've never met the requirements to make [that guy] show up with any character of mine, much less seen him myself. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
I'm 98% certain I've never researched [that guy] in the Beastmster's shop -- I almost never use it, and I've never had the need to research [that guy]. I usually do my researching over on oook, anyway. 
</p>
</li>
</ol>

